    summary: "US household wealth remains highly concentrated, with the top 1% holding roughly 31.9% of net worth versus 2.5% for the bottom half as of Q4 2025, while only about 42% of small employer firms that apply for financing get the full amount they seek. These distribution and access-to-credit gaps define where inclusive growth is measured.",
